2. Scope and Consent
2.1. You accept this Privacy Policy when You sign up for, access, or use Our products, services, content, features, technologies or functions offered on Our Website and all related sites, applications, and services. We may amend this policy at any time by posting a revised version on Our Website. The revised version will be effective at the time We post it.
2.2. You acknowledge and agree that it is Your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically and become aware of amendments. Your continued using of the Our Website, products and services will be deemed as Your acceptance of those changes.
3. Collection of Personal Information
3.1. We collect the following types of personal information in order to provide You with the use of and access to Our Website, products, applications, services and tools, and to help Us personalize and improve Your experience.
3.2. Information we collect automatically: When you visit the Website or use Our products, applications, services and tools, We collect information sent to us by Your computer, mobile phone or other access device. The information sent to Us includes but is not limited to the following: data about the pages You access, device type, connection information, mobile network information, advertisement placement statistics, statistics on page views, traffic to and from the sites, referral URL, ad data, and standard web log data and other information. We may use geo-location information (country, region, city from IP) for ad targeting but we do not collect this info. We do not use hyper-local targeting (less than 3 km radius).
3.3. Information You provide to Us: We may collect and store any information You enter on the Website or You provide to Us in context of using Our Website, applications, products, services, or tools.
3.4. When you visit the Website or use Our products, applications, services and tools, We also collect information about your transactions and Your activities. In addition, if You open a personal account on the Website, We may collect the following types of information:
3.4.1. Contact information, such as Your name or companyВ’s name, address, phone, email and other similar information.
3.4.2. Financial information, such as the full bank account numbers and/or credit card numbers that You link to Your account or give Us when You use Our products, applications, services and tools.
3.4.3. Detailed personal information such as Your date of birth or national ID number, country of legal entityВ’s registration, legal entityВ’s registration number etc.
3.5. Any content uploaded by You on the Website becomes published content and is not considered personal information subject to this Privacy Policy. We are not responsible for Your personal information which voluntarily was made accessible by You to the public.
4. Use the Personal Information We Collect
4.1. Our primary purpose in collecting personal information is to provide You with a secure, smooth, efficient, and customized experience. We may use Your personal information to:
4.1.1. provide services, products and customer support;
4.1.2. process transactions and send notices about Your transactions;
4.1.3. collect fees;
4.1.4. resolve disputes and troubleshoot problems;
4.1.5. prevent potentially prohibited or illegal activities;
4.1.6. enforce Our Agreement;
4.1.7. customize, measure, and improve Our Website, its content, products, applications, services, etc.;
4.1.8. contact You by email messaging;
4.1.9. compare information for accuracy and verify it with third parties.
4.2. Your Personal Information collected by Us will be retained for as long as permitted by applicable law or necessary depending on the respective purpose of collection and shall be deleted when they no longer serve one of the above-mentioned purposes or shall be anonymized and therefore will no longer constitute Personal Information. It is clarified that in no case the retention period should exceed the 5 years from the date of collection. Once we have deleted or anonymized your Personal Information, you will not be able to exercise the right to access, the right to erasure, the right to rectification or the right to data portability.
